<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec_fibonacci">
  <title>Fibonacci Numbers</title>
  <p>
    The <em>Fibonacci
    <fn>
      Named after Leonardo Pisano Fibonacci (1170<ndash/>1250).
    </fn>
    numbers</em> are a sequence of integers defined recursively through
    <md>
      <mrow>f_0 \amp = 0</mrow>
      <mrow>f_1 \amp = 1</mrow>
      <mrow>f_n \amp = f_{n-1} + f_{n-2} \qquad \text{ for \(n \geq
      2\) }</mrow>
    </md>.
        <idx><h>Fibonacci numbers</h></idx>
  </p>
  <p>
    Let <m>F(z) = \s f_k \, z^k</m>.
    <ol marker="1. ">
      <li>
        <p>
          Show that <m>F</m> has a positive radius of convergence.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Show that the recurrence relation among the <m>f_n</m>
          implies that 
          <m>F(z) = \frac{z}{1 - z - z^2}</m>. (<em>Hint</em>: Write
          down the power series of <m>z \, F(z)</m> and 
          <m>z^2 \, F(z)</m> and rearrange both so that you can easily
          add.) 
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Verify that
          <me>
            \Res_{z=0} \left( \frac{1}{z^n (1 - z - z^2)} \right) \ = \ f_n\,
          </me>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Use the Residue <xref ref="residuethm"/>
          to derive an identity for <m>f_n</m>. (<em>Hint</em>: Integrate
          <me>
            \frac{1}{z^n (1 - z - z^2)}
          </me>
          around <m>C[0,R]</m> and show that this integral vanishes as
          <m>R \to \infty</m>.) 
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Generalize to other sequences defined by recurrence relations,
          e.g., the <em>Tribonacci numbers
            <idx><h>Tribonacci numbers</h></idx>
          </em>
          <md>
            <mrow>t_0 \amp = 0</mrow>
            <mrow>t_1 \amp = 0</mrow>
            <mrow>t_2 \amp = 1</mrow>
            <mrow>t_n \amp = t_{n-1} + t_{n-2} + t_{n-3} \qquad \text{
            for \(n \geq 3\). }</mrow> 
          </md>
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>
</section>
